        name: "Dr Kim de Graaf",
        title: "Senior Lecturer in Civil Engineering - UoW",
        company: "UoW",
        bio: "Kim is a senior lecturer in Civil Engineering at the University of Waikato and a Chartered Professional Geotechnical Engineer with strong industry links. She has over 10 years of experience as a geotechnical engineer through various building and infrastructure projects. After returning to academia in 2021, Kim has focussed her research interests on the behaviour of unusual NZ soils, slope instability, landslides and the use of geotechnical waste to create 3D printable sustainable concrete. Kim is also leading a research group in the early stages of the development of an AR system to support communities in understanding their risk to natural hazards and potential to improve resilience.",
        image: "https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/646ab5895264c7470e0c89f5/671b35c8e36df2b7c7cf4180_Screen%20Shot%202024-10-25%20at%207.07.56%20PM.png",
