        bio: "Margaret Paiti has a solid understanding of Āotearoa's educational system. With over twenty-five years of experience across a diverse range of roles, she's fully familiar with both the challenges and opportunities within STEM education. Committed to collaboration, Margaret's goal is to strengthen relationships among various groups, driving meaningful change. A passionate advocate for STEM, she urges young people, especially those who are underserved, to delve into these fields. Her active role with the Web Access Waikato Trust demonstrates her commitment to digital inclusion. Additionally, her contributions to the Waikato Tertiary Tech Alliance emphasise her dedication to expanding STEM opportunities.‍",
